---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words with Prefix AUTO in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Bingo Strategy"
  description="Master AUTO prefix words in Scrabble. Top plays include AUTOPSY (12pts), AUTOGRAPH (15pts), AUTOMATE (10pts). Strategy for using this 4-tile prefix to land bingos."
  keywords="words with prefix auto scrabble, auto words scrabble, autopsy scrabble points, auto bingo scrabble, auto prefix strategy, scrabble words starting with auto"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article", "headline": "Words with Prefix AUTO in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Bingo Strategy", "description": "Master AUTO prefix words in Scrabble. Top plays include AUTOPSY, AUTOGRAPH, AUTOMATE. Strategy for 4-tile prefix bingos.", "datePublished": "2026-06-23", "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }, "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" }, "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-with-prefix-auto" } })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [ { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best AUTO prefix words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top AUTO words include AUTOPSY (12pts), AUTOGRAPH (15pts), AUTOMATE (10pts), AUTOCRAT (10pts), and AUTONOMY (13pts). AUTOPSY is the best short play at 12 points without needing a bingo." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can AUTO help me get a bingo in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! AUTO is a strong bingo prefix. At 4 tiles, you need only 3 more to reach the 7-tile bingo bonus. Words like AUTOMATE, AUTOPILOT, and AUTOGRAPH are all achievable bingo plays." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is AUTO itself a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, AUTO is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS worth 4 points. Its plural AUTOS is also valid. But using it as a bingo prefix is far more valuable strategically." } } ] })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Prefix Guides</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words with Prefix AUTO in Scrabble</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">AUTO is one of the most versatile prefixes in Scrabble. At just 4 tiles (all common, low-value letters), it opens the door to dozens of valid words — including several bingo candidates. Whether you're aiming for AUTOPSY's 12 points or fishing for a full 7-letter bingo, understanding AUTO words gives you a serious edge.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Prefix Tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Extensions</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles to Bingo</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top AUTO Words by Score</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">AUTOPSY — 12 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 letters. Examination of a body. Y tile adds 4 points. Highest-scoring non-bingo AUTO word.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">AUTOGRAPH — 15 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 letters. A signature. H(4) and G(2) push this high. Bingo candidate on open boards.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">AUTONOMY — 13 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. Self-governance. Y(4) makes this a strong bingo at 63 total with bonus.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">AUTOMATE — 10 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. To make automatic. All common tiles — highly achievable bingo worth 60 total.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More High-Value AUTO Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AUTOCRAT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AUTOTYPE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AUTOLYSE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AUTOBAHN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AUTOGENY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AUTODYNE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AUTO Bingo Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Only 3 more tiles needed:</span> With AUTO on your rack (4 tiles), you need just 3 more for the 7-tile bingo threshold. Better odds than most prefixes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Common completions:</span> AUTOMATE needs M-A-T-E (shares A with prefix). AUTOCRAT needs C-R-A-T. Look for common consonants on your rack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play through existing letters:</span> If the board has M, A, T, or E, you might complete AUTOMATE using an existing tile — needing only 6 from your rack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack leave quality:</span> If you keep A-U-T-O on your rack, you have excellent bingo potential next turn. Sacrifice points now for 50+ bonus later.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AUTO as a Standalone Word</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Quick Fact</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AUTO itself is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS (4 points). Its plural <span class="text-white font-medium">AUTOS</span> (5pts) is also valid. But strategically, you're almost always better using AUTO as a prefix rather than playing it alone — the bingo potential far outweighs 4-5 base points.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-mono/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix MONO: Single-Meaning Power Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-multi/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix MULTI: Many-Meaning Bingo Stems</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all AUTO words instantly — enter your tiles and see every valid play</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
